headline: BofA Stays Bearish on C3.ai (AI), Sees Limited Upside Amid Rising AI Competition
summary: C3.ai, Inc. (NYSE:AI) is one of the 10 AI Stocks Making Waves on Wall Street. On January 30, BofA Securities analyst Brad Sills lowered the price target on the stock to $10.00 (from $14.00) while maintaining an “Underperform” rating. The firm sees weak growth visibility, peer discount, and limited upside until a clearer defensibility and growth […]

headline: Wall Street banks, crypto leaders set to meet in Washington with landmark Clarity Act hanging in the balance

headline: Bank Of America’s Bigger Flutter Stake And What It Might Signal
summary: Bank of America has disclosed a significant increase in its stake in Flutter Entertainment (NYSE:FLUT), crossing ownership thresholds above 5% and then to about 13% of total voting rights. The higher exposure was reported over recent weeks, reflecting material changes in the shareholder base of the global online betting and gaming group. These threshold crossings were publicly disclosed through regulatory filings, highlighting the scale of institutional interest in Flutter’s equity. Flutter...
